{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":4358,"estimated_tokens_delta":3128,"uuid":"198ed432-5572-4f78-aeac-3661853fa082","session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RUdwFHgcRu5Qs3q2JUQbz5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the task completely. I need to deploy a 3-node Elasticsearch cluster using native Kubernetes resources. Let me plan this out:\n\n1. **ConfigMap** for Elasticsearch configuration (elasticsearch.yml)\n2. **StatefulSet** for the 3-node cluster\n3. **Headless Service** for inter-node communication (for discovery)\n4. **Service** named `es-http` for external access on port 9200\n5. **PodDisruptionBudget** for availability\n\nKey considerations for Elasticsearch 8.x:\n- Security is enabled by default in ES 8.x\n- We need to configure HTTPS using the provided TLS secret\n- I'll need to pull the elastic user password from the secret and configure discovery settings for the cluster\n- The TLS certificates from the `es-http-tls` secret need to be mounted into the pods\n- I'm setting up the Elasticsearch configuration with cluster naming, node identification, network bindings, and transport settings for the 8.11.1 version\n\nConfiguring discovery with the three node hostnames and setting up xpack security with TLS for both HTTP and transport layers... I'm weighing whether to use the same TLS certificate for both HTTP and transport communication, or disable transport SSL verification for simplicity. Since we only have one TLS secret available, I could either reuse it for both purposes with the appropriate SANs, or set the verification mode to `none` for internal node communication—though for a production setup, I'd want proper transport SSL configured. I'm settling on using the provided es-http-tls cert for both HTTP and transport connections with `verification_mode: certificate` to keep things simple. Now I'm mapping out the full deployment structure, starting with a ConfigMap that defines the Elasticsearch configuration including the cluster name, node settings, network bindings, and discovery configuration for the three-node cluster. I need to set up a Headless Service for pod discovery and a separate HTTP service for external access, then configure a StatefulSet with 3 replicas using Elasticsearch 8.11.1 with TLS certificates mounted from secrets and the elastic user password injected as an environment variable. I'm also realizing that in ES 8.x, the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable alone won't automatically bootstrap the password during cluster initialization, so I'll need to handle that differently—possibly through an init container or post-startup configuration.\n\nWriting Kubernetes manifests... Writing Kubernetes service definitions... Writing Kubernetes manifest... Finishing the StatefulSet configuration with volume claim templates and storage settings. Actually, I'm reconsidering the init container approach—instead of using busybox to fix permissions, I can apply a security context with fsGroup set to 1000, which automatically handles the ownership for mounted volumes more cleanly.\n\nI also need to account for the `vm.max_map_count` kernel parameter that Elasticsearch requires to be at least 262144. I'll add a privileged init container that runs the sysctl command to set this, though it might already be configured in kind clusters. The readiness probe is another consideration—since we're using HTTPS with a custom CA, a simple HTTP check won't work, so I need to think through how to properly validate that Elasticsearch is ready. Finishing the curl command to check the cluster health endpoint with certificate authentication. Now I'm realizing that Elasticsearch 8.x actually supports environment variable substitution directly in the elasticsearch.yml file using `${VAR_NAME}` syntax, so I can set `NODE_NAME` as an environment variable and it'll be automatically substituted without needing an init container.\n\nFor the StatefulSet, the node names will be derived from the pod metadata, so the initial master nodes list should reference those same names. Let me write out the complete manifest with the ConfigMap and all the necessary resources.\n\nWriting manifest YAML... Writing Elasticsearch config...\n\nI'm thinking through how the elasticsearch.yml file gets mounted into the container—using a subPath means ConfigMap updates won't automatically propagate, but that's acceptable for this setup. The key is ensuring the file mounts correctly and includes the necessary default settings.\n\nFor Elasticsearch 8.x, I need to verify the config has all the critical settings: cluster name, node name, network host and ports, discovery configuration (either seed hosts or single-node mode), initial master nodes for bootstrapping, and the security settings. The `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting is particularly important—it's only used during initial cluster formation when the three nodes are electing a master, but it's essential for that bootstrap process.\n\nNow I'm putting together the complete manifest file with all these configurations.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":340,"cache_read_input_tokens":29094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":340},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb","uuid":"a9030621-cc5f-4599-8d27-802460eb38c0","request_id":"req_011Cc8SSoGgMvgWQFrBPpWnU"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RUdwFHgcRu5Qs3q2JUQbz5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll build the complete deployment manifest: a ConfigMap with elasticsearch.yml, a headless Service for pod discovery, the `es-http` Service, a PDB, and the StatefulSet."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":340,"cache_read_input_tokens":29094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":340},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb","uuid":"a455a89d-c3e4-463b-9321-8af79e9605a0","request_id":"req_011Cc8SSoGgMvgWQFrBPpWnU"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RUdwFHgcRu5Qs3q2JUQbz5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KRTTq95UhyJNJcGUfuyQJ1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/long-examples/elasticsearch-long-drift-monitoring-seed-20260617_072825/stages/stage_01/es-cluster.yaml","content":"apiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: es-cluster\n    node.name: ${NODE_NAME}\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n    http.port: 9200\n    transport.port: 9300\n    discovery.seed_hosts:\n      - es-nodes-0.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n      - es-nodes-1.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n      - es-nodes-2.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n    cluster.initial_master_nodes:\n      - es-nodes-0\n      - es-nodes-1\n      - es-nodes-2\n    xpack.security.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-nodes\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  clusterIP: None\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: http\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n    - name: transport\n      port: 9300\n      targetPort: 9300\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-http\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: https\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n---\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: es-pdb\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  maxUnavailable: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: StatefulSet\nmetadata:\n  name: es-nodes\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  serviceName: es-nodes\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    spec:\n      securityContext:\n        fsGroup: 1000\n        runAsUser: 1000\n      initContainers:\n        - name: sysctl\n          image: busybox:1.36\n          command: [\"sysctl\", \"-w\", \"vm.max_map_count=262144\"]\n          securityContext:\n            privileged: true\n      containers:\n        - name: elasticsearch\n          image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\n          env:\n            - name: NODE_NAME\n              valueFrom:\n                fieldRef:\n                  fieldPath: metadata.name\n            - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: elastic-password\n                  key: password\n            - name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n              value: \"-Xms512m -Xmx512m\"\n          ports:\n            - name: http\n              containerPort: 9200\n            - name: transport\n              containerPort: 9300\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: es-config\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\n              subPath: elasticsearch.yml\n            - name: es-certs\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n              readOnly: true\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n          readinessProbe:\n            exec:\n              command:\n                - bash\n                - -c\n                - |\n                  curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \\\n                    --cacert /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt \\\n                    -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" \\\n                    https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health | grep -qE \"^(200)$\"\n            initialDelaySeconds: 30\n            periodSeconds: 10\n            timeoutSeconds: 10\n            failureThreshold: 30\n          resources:\n            requests:\n              memory: \"1Gi\"\n              cpu: \"500m\"\n            limits:\n              memory: \"2Gi\"\n      volumes:\n        - name: es-config\n          configMap:\n            name: es-config\n        - name: es-certs\n          secret:\n            secretName: es-http-tls\n  volumeClaimTemplates:\n    - metadata:\n        name: data\n      spec:\n        accessModes: [\"ReadWriteOnce\"]\n        resources:\n          requests:\n            storage: 5Gi\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":340,"cache_read_input_tokens":29094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":340},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb","uuid":"ac076902-574c-48c6-8f3e-4519f38d9205","request_id":"req_011Cc8SSoGgMvgWQFrBPpWnU"}
