{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DPNbkLD9J2q6evswGkPJmm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ES node is running and trying to resolve the other nodes. The DNS for `es-nodes-1.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` is not resolving yet because those pods haven't started. This is expected behavior - the cluster is bootstrapping as the StatefulSet creates pods sequentially (0, 1, 2).\n\nThe es-nodes-0 pod is in `Running` state (but not Ready because the readiness probe is checking for cluster health which requires all 3 nodes). This is normal - it's waiting for the other nodes.\n\nThe StatefulSet should create pods sequentially (0, then 1, then 2). \n\nI'm realizing there's a bootstrapping issue here - the default `OrderedReady` policy means the StatefulSet won't start pod 1 until pod 0 is Ready, but pod 0 can't become Ready until the cluster is formed with all 3 nodes. This is a classic chicken-and-egg problem that needs a different approach to resolve.\n\nThe fix is to switch to `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all three pods launch at once, allowing them to discover each other and form the cluster without waiting for sequential readiness checks.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":873,"cache_read_input_tokens":39688,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":873},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb","uuid":"2a638509-26c2-47c9-aa53-c41cf3991473","request_id":"req_011Cc8Tdd5BhfahS7B4yy3ZZ"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DPNbkLD9J2q6evswGkPJmm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ES node-0 is running but waiting for the other nodes. The problem is the default `OrderedReady` policy — pod-0 won't be `Ready` until the cluster forms (needs all 3 nodes), but pods 1 and 2 won't start until pod-0 is `Ready`. Need `Parallel` pod management:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":873,"cache_read_input_tokens":39688,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":873},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb","uuid":"c96aeaea-8da1-46ee-9e23-be2194a58c70","request_id":"req_011Cc8Tdd5BhfahS7B4yy3ZZ"}
