{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011KbipUqZoVBL7QK1vpaZPd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The headless service DNS isn't resolving for `es-nodes-1` and `es-nodes-2`. This means the DNS isn't mapping those pods to their IPs. The headless service is likely not working correctly because the pods aren't ready yet (headless service DNS requires pods to be ready by default).\n\nWait, actually for a headless service (ClusterIP: None), DNS resolution for individual pods should work even when the pods are not ready, IF the service has `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`. Otherwise, by default, DNS only resolves to ready pods.\n\nSince none of the pods are Ready (readiness probe isn't passing), the headless service doesn't return any endpoints for `es-nodes-1.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` because those pods aren't ready.\nI'm seeing a circular dependency here: the pods need to form a cluster to become ready, but they can't communicate with each other until DNS resolves their addresses, which won't happen until they're ready. The solution is to add `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` to the headless service so DNS resolves even for not-ready pods, breaking this deadlock.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1062,"cache_read_input_tokens":44411,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1062},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb","uuid":"f93a3d84-42bd-4c8d-ae2f-4f50f2751729","request_id":"req_011Cc8Ud5XEpwtFK2mD4omyP"}
