{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FWhkEtMq98YmVrXf1WGvp5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is fully deployed and operational. Here's what was created:\n\n- **ConfigMap `es-config`** — `elasticsearch.yml` with cluster settings, TLS paths, and `${NODE_NAME}` interpolation for per-pod identity\n- **StatefulSet `es-nodes`** (3/3 Ready) — `Parallel` pod management policy so all 3 pods start simultaneously (avoiding the chicken-and-egg deadlock where OrderedReady would block pod-1 waiting for pod-0's readiness, which requires pod-1 to exist)\n- **Headless Service `es-nodes`** with `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` — makes pod DNS (`es-nodes-N.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc`) resolve before pods are ready (needed for initial cluster discovery)\n- **Service `es-http`** — ClusterIP on port 9200 for HTTPS client access\n- **PDB `es-pdb`** — `maxUnavailable: 1` to protect quorum\n\nCluster is **green**, 3 data nodes, reads and writes succeed through `es-http` at `https://es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9200`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391,"cache_read_input_tokens":52757,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":391},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c167305-9545-45b5-a765-3255f73527fb","uuid":"06dfd0f9-9e4a-46f0-afc3-ea6820991f21","request_id":"req_011Cc8UngEZBSmHjQx5qvPke"}
